  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We study some examples of minimal length curves in homogeneous spaces of <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi mathvariant="script">B</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="script">H</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> under a left action of a unitary group. Recent results relate these curves with the existence of minimal (with respect to a quotient norm) anti-Hermitian operators Z in the tangent space of the starting point. We show minimal curves that are not of this type but nevertheless can be approximated uniformly by those.</subfield>
